         <abstract>
            <p>Acute inflationary pressures in the U. S. have so far failed to respond to fiscal and monetary treatment. However, a correction may be on the way. If the American Commitment in Southeast Asia runs down as promised and current recessionary trends continue, inflation may well fall to an acceptable rate without the use of wage and price controls-- which would work poorly and inequitably if introduced.</p>
          </abstract>
